            <title>[SUREFIRE-2] [patch included] surefire skips all tests and reports succes when encountering a class that doesn&apos;t extend TestCase</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-2</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Some folks have reported that their JUnit test aren&apos;t being executed. This happens when one of the test&lt;br/&gt;
classes doesn&apos;t extend TestCase.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve improved error handling and confinuation of testcase execution in case of battery execution failure,&lt;br/&gt;
marking failures as errors, and improved recognition of testcase classes: now you JUnitBattery falls&lt;br/&gt;
back to AbstractBattery if it encounters a POJO, after trying to find the TestCase api method signatures&lt;br/&gt;
on the POJO first.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
